    <briefdescription>
<para>Attach to: Quit Button (Canvas &gt; Quit Button). </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>No GameManager needed. Completely self-contained.</para>
<para>SETUP:<orderedlist>
<listitem><para>First, build the popup panel in your scene (see steps below).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Select &quot;Quit Button&quot; in the Hierarchy.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Add Component → <ref refid="class_quit_popup_manager" kindref="compound">QuitPopupManager</ref>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Drag your popup panel into the Quit Popup Panel slot.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Drag the Yes and No buttons (inside the popup) into their slots.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Type your main menu scene name into Main Menu Scene Name. Must match exactly what&apos;s in File &gt; Build Settings.</para>
</listitem></orderedlist>
</para>
<para>HOW TO BUILD THE POPUP PANEL: a. Right-click Canvas → UI → Panel. Rename it &quot;Quit Popup Panel&quot;. b. Give it a dark semi-transparent background colour. c. Resize it to a small centred box (e.g. 400 x 200). d. Inside it, add: • UI &gt; Text (TMP) — write &quot;Do you want to leave the game?&quot; • UI &gt; Button (TMP) — rename &quot;Yes Button&quot;, set label text to &quot;Yes&quot; • UI &gt; Button (TMP) — rename &quot;No Button&quot;, set label text to &quot;No&quot; e. The panel will hide itself automatically on Play via CanvasGroup — you do NOT need to set it inactive in the Inspector. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
